# 📝 To-Do List Application
### DecodeLabs Python Internship — Project 1 | Batch 2026

---

## 📌 Overview

A command-line To-Do List application built with Python.
This project focuses on **Data Management** — storing, 
retrieving, and displaying tasks through pure programmatic logic.

---

## ✨ Features

- ✅ Add new tasks
- 📋 View all saved tasks with numbering
- 💾 Tasks saved to file — data persists after closing!
- ⚠️ Empty task validation
- 🔢 Total task count display
- 👋 Graceful exit with goodbye message

---

## 💡 Concepts Used

| Concept | Usage |
|---------|-------|
| `list` | Storing all tasks |
| `append()` | Adding new tasks |
| `for` loop | Displaying tasks |
| `while` loop | Keeping program running |
| `if/elif/else` | Menu choices |
| `enumerate()` | Numbered task list |
| `try/except` | File not found handling |
| File Handling | Persistent data storage |
| Functions | Clean, organized code |

---

## ▶️ How to Run

```bash
python todolist.py
```

